title: Mt Charlie Reserve Flora Riddells Creek

items.title: Olearia glandulosa
items.content_text: Approaching the end of its flowering time.

items.title: Cassytha pubescens s.s.
items.content_text: New species record for Mt Charlie Reserve. Only the second plant I've seen in the area (the other at Mt Teneriffe).

items.title: Lobelia gibbosa sensu Walsh  Albrecht & Knox (2010)
items.content_text: Confirmed ID from seed etc. About two dozen plants over 10x10m. No other populations of this species are known in Riddells Creek.
tags: id~Lobelia gibbosa sensu Walsh  Albrecht & Knox (2010)

items.title: Prostanthera lasianthos var. lasianthos
items.content_text: Note eggs in upper right corner of 2nd photo.

items.title: Xanthorrhoea australis
items.content_text: Two plants flowering following a late burn (some time Autumn-Winter, not sure when).

items.title: Plantago debilis
items.content_text: Sepals about 1.5mm long. Flower/fruit is much smaller than for P. varia. This plant found in a damper roadside, reconfirms the species for Riddells Creek as found by I. Lunt in 1984/5. First time I've seen it in Riddells Creek.

items.title: Stylidium armeria subsp. armeria
items.content_text: This plant about 1.2m tall, very long leaves and large flowers (relative to the other subsp. depicted nearby in observation 11370).

items.title: Stylidium armeria subsp. pilosifolium
items.content_text: Recent burn has revealed numerous plants (we saw 25ish so possibly 100ish overall) spread over a narrow area with limits as detailed by the 3 plants depicted here.

items.title: Diptera spp., Hydrocotyle laxiflora
items.content_text: Tiny flies over Stinking Pennywort.

items.title: Eucalyptus globulus subsp. bicostata
items.content_text: This subspecies is defined by fruit in 3s and fruit sessile (stalkless). Small copse of young trees - not aware of any other populations in Riddells Creek. Possibly be a weed but hard to tell.

items.title: Dispar compacta, Senecio linearifolius var. linearifolius
Olearia glandulosa
items.content_text: Upright shrub, about 2.5m tall. Only one plant seen. Not formally recorded in Macedon Range since Ian Lunt's 1984 study. Probably locally very rare.

items.title: Wahlenbergia stricta subsp. stricta
items.content_text: Showing campanulate (bell-shaped) flower tube.

items.title: Conium maculatum
items.content_text: A declared noxious weed.

items.title: Prunella vulgaris
items.content_text: In a swampy area.

items.title: Sambucus gaudichaudiana
items.content_text: Not previously recorded in Riddells Creek. Growing on the edge of Charlies Creek.

items.title: Olearia rugosa subsp. rugosa
items.content_text: Previously unknown here. Now subsp. rugosa.

items.title: Coprosma quadrifida
items.content_text: First record of this species for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Acacia mucronata subsp. longifolia
items.content_text: Location approximate.

items.title: Pterostylis parviflora s.s.
items.content_text: Green tip = P. parviflora s.s.. Look is very different to P. sp. aff. parviflora (Southern Victoria) plants nearby on Barrm Birrm & Pyrete. One plant seen. Reddening old flowers is more like P. sp. aff. parviflora (Southern Victoria). Photo David Francis.

items.title: 58 ids
items.content_text: Short walk along Mt Charlie Rd from Mt Teneriffe Rd intersection. Location is where I stopped and turned back (at a large yellow Euc, covered in yellow lichen). This road has Mt Teneriffe on one side and Mt Charlie of the other, with creek running alongsi

items.title: 81 ids
items.content_text: Walk with David Francis from Rowallan Scout Camp on Mt Kent Rd, over the top to the bare area and down to the Eatons Rd loop track. Location is near top of hill.

items.title: Banksia marginata
items.content_text: Open, lanky shrubs, mostly to about 2m tall. The most common mid-level shrub in this part of the reserve.

items.title: Olearia rugosa subsp. rugosa
items.content_text: One small patch in a lovely spot among Banksia marginata, Correa reflexa var. reflexa (cream) and Grass Trees. Location approximate. Now subsp. rugosa.

items.title: Eucalyptus globulus subsp. bicostata
items.content_text: Small population of young trees.

items.title: Stylidium armeria subsp. pilosifolium
items.content_text: Just a few plants noticed in a dry, shaly area with larger than normal (for Mt Charlie Reserve) inter-tussock spaces.

items.title: 89 ids
items.content_text: Survey walking around the circular path/road accessed from Eatons Road. Location is iPhone GPS taken at start/finish point on Eatons Rd..
